frequencyConnectedness v0.2.4 (Release date: 2023-02-23)
==============

Changes:

* Added plotting method for rolling spillovers that plots a specific element within the list of tables.
* Small cleanup.

frequencyConnectedness v0.2.3 (Release date: 2020-11-10)
==============

Changes:

* Added check in rolling spillovers for the NA elements. Those would typically result in errors in estimation that might be more cryptic than just reflecting that user passed data with NAs inside the data. Optional argument to disable.

frequencyConnectedness v0.2.2 (Release date: 2020-02-04)
==============

Changes:

* Fixed documentation bugs as per checks on CRAN.


frequencyConnectedness v0.2.1 (Release date: 2018-09-23)
==============

Changes:

* Based on the pull request #2, the warning has been removed for cases when the class of data is longer than 1. Thanks go to `regisely`.

* Reference to the published paper is now everywhere.


frequencyConnectedness v0.2.0 (Release date: 2017-07-12)
==============

Changes:

* The way to call the functions has been redesigned and whole new system of S3 functions has been implemented. There are now new concise functions for plotting and printing. Refer to the front page on the github.com/tomaskrehlik/frequencyConnectedness


frequencyConnectedness v0.1.6 (Release date: 2017-06-09)
==============

Changes:

* The BK and DY spillovers did not sum to the same values for cases when the parameter table = F. Added test case for this.